The paper focuses on image-based object detection, specifically pedestrian detection, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also deals with domain adaptation for classifiers, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions revisiting the source-domain samples, which is a common technique in cryptography (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
